## Best Practices

{% alert value="<strong>Icon Selection:</strong> Choose icons that clearly represent your content. The component supports 30+ built-in icons." type="info" /%}

{% alert value="<strong>Title Length:</strong> Keep titles concise (1-4 words) for better visual impact and readability." type="info" /%}

{% alert value="<strong>Description Length:</strong> Aim for 10-25 words in descriptions. Longer text is supported but may affect layout." type="warning" /%}

{% alert value="<strong>Grid Layout:</strong> IconCards work best in grid layouts. Consider grouping related cards together." type="info" /%}

## Available Icons

The component currently supports these icons:

**Technology**: `code`, `database`, `server`, `cloud`, `desktop`, `mobile`, `tablet`, `wifi`, `signal`, `battery`, `plug`

**Interface**: `gear`, `sidebar`, `list`, `list-dashes`, `magnifying-glass`, `printer`, `images`

**Security**: `lock`, `key`, `shield`

**General**: `pen`, `rocket`, `heart`, `star`, `lightning`, `globe`, `person-arms-spread`, `parachute`, `circle-half`

## Customization

{% accordion title="Adding New Icons" %}
To add new icons, modify the `iconMap` in the IconCard component:

```typescript
const iconMap: Record<string, string> = {
    'your-icon-name': 'ðŸ†•',
    // ... other icons
};
```

You can use any emoji or consider integrating with icon libraries like Heroicons or Lucide.
{% /accordion %}

{% accordion title="Styling Customization" %}
The component uses theme-aware CSS classes that automatically adapt to your site's color scheme:

- `border-theme-primary` - Card border
- `bg-theme-primary` - Card background
- `text-theme-primary` - Title color
- `text-theme-secondary` - Description color
- `hover:bg-theme-secondary` - Hover state

Modify your theme CSS to customize the appearance.
{% /accordion %}
